	To elect six Directors to serve until the next Annual Meeting of Shareholders and until their successors are elected and qualified;









	2.



	To consider and ratify the appointment of Freed Maxick CPAs, P.C. as the Company’s independent registered public accounting
	firm for the 2017 fiscal year;









	3.



	To transact such other business as may properly come before the meeting or any adjournments thereof.




	 


	Only shareholders
	of record at the close of business on March 16, 2017 are entitled to notice of and to vote at the meeting or any adjournments thereof.


	 




	 


